Photosynthesis is a process involving carbon dioxide, water, glucose, oxygen, and sunlight. Which is the correct chemical equation for photosynthesis?
A. O_{2} + H_{2}O + energy -> C_{6}H_{12}O_{6} + CO_{2}
B. CO_{2} + H_{2}O -> C_{6}H_{6}O_{3} + O_{2} + energy
C. 6O_{2} + 6H_{2}O -> C_{6}H_{12}O_{6} + 6CO_{2} + energy
D. 6CO_{2} + 6H_{2}O + energy -> C_{6}H_{12}O_{6} + 6O_{2}

Which of these is an element?
A. KBr
B. O_{2}
C. 2KCl
D. FeO_{2}

Examine each of these chemical equations to determine which equation is correctly balanced.
A. Mg(NO_{3})_{2} + K_{2}CO_{3} -> MgCO_{3} + KNO_{3}
B. Mg(NO_{3})_{2} + K_{2}CO_{3} -> MgCO_{3} + 2KNO_{3}
C. 2Mg(NO_{3})_{2} + K_{2}CO_{3} -> 2MgCO_{3} + KNO_{3}
D. Mg(NO_{3})_{2} + 2K_{2}CO_{3} -> MgCO_{3} + 2KNO_{3}

Which of the following represents the process of photosynthesis?
A. C_{6}H_{12}O_{6} -> 6CO_{2} + 6H_{2}O
B. 6CO_{2} + 6H_{2}O -> C_{6}H_{12}O_{6} +6O_{2}
C. 2H_{2}O -> 2H_{2} + O_{2}
D. 2H_{2} + O_{2} -> 2H_{2}O

Magnesium bromide is one of the most abundant compounds found in sea water. Which formula correctly represents magnesium bromide?
A. MgBr
B. MgBr_{2}
C. Mg_{2}Br
D. Mg_{3}Br_{2}

Which of the following is a correctly written chemical equation that demonstrates the conservation of mass?
A. Mg + HCl -> H_{2} + MgCl_{2}
B. H_{2}O + CO_{2} -> H_{2}CO_{3}
C. KClO_{3} -> KCl + O_{2}
D. H_{2} + O_{2} -> H_{2}O

An aluminum ion has a charge of +3, and an oxide ion has a charge of -2. Which would be the product of a reaction between these two elements?
A. Al_{2}O
B. Al_{2}O_{3}
C. 2AlO_{3}
D. Al_{3}O_{2}

A student placed a living green plant in an airtight, transparent container filled with air from the room. The container was exposed to sunlight for one week. At the end of the week the student was to determine which gases had increased in concentration. Assuming enough water and carbon dioxide were available for the proper growth of the plant, which gas would you expect to be present in increased concentration?
A. C
B. NO_{2}
C. O_{2}
D. CO

Significant destruction of a forest habitat will increase which gas in the atmosphere?
A. CO_{2}
B. NO_{2}
C. O_{2}
D. N_{2}

If HCl is added to Zn, what would be an expected product?
A. Cl_{2}
B. HZn
C. ZnCl
D. ZnCl_{2}
